Heat water to boiling in medium saucepan. Stir in rice. Remove from heat and let stand, covered, 5 minutes. Heat oil in 12-inch non-stick skillet until hot. Add chicken, onion and pepper; cook, stirring frequently until chicken is no longer pink in color, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 5 minutes. Stir in rice and serve immediately.